Package gov.nasa.jpl.aerie.merlin.timeline.effects

Interface Projection<Event,​Effect>

Type Parameters:
Event - The type of event to be mapped into effects.
Effect - The type of effect that will be combined according to the event graph structure.
All Superinterfaces:
EffectTrait<Effect>
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractProjection, EventGraphProjection
public interface Projection<Event,​Effect> extends EffectTrait<Effect>
A projection from an EventGraph to some accumulated effect type.

Projection extends EffectTrait by requiring a mapping from events to effects. Just as EffectTrait can be thought of as allowing the construction of algebraic expressions over effects, Projection further allows atomic events to be used as variables in these expressions.

    • from

      static <Event,​ Effect> Projection<Event,​Effect> from​(EffectTrait<Effect> trait, Function<Event,​Effect> interpretation)
      A factory method for constructing projections from an EffectTrait and an interpretation of events in that trait. A Projection is an EffectTrait with an additionam function from events to effects. This factory method allows a Projection to be constructed from these components without requiring a new class declaration.
      Type Parameters:
      Event - The type of event to project from.
      Effect - The type of effect to project onto.
      Parameters:
      trait - The trait against which the EffectTrait.empty(), EffectTrait.sequentially(Effect, Effect), and EffectTrait.concurrently(Effect, Effect) methods shall be implemented.
      interpretation - The interpretation of events as effects against which the atom(Event) method shall be implemented.
      Returns:
      A Projection behaving as a composite of the given effect trait and event interpretation.
